item.description: There is some confusion about the name interlucens which may be a more northern species.

item.title: Endoxyla spp.
item.dc:creator: koolah
item.description: This is also the female of the Undescribed species however there is a major loss of scales on the wings. It gives the appearance of brown colour and you can see the wing veins clearly. There is also some damage around the head area. Surprising she could still navigate.

item.title: Nataxa flavescens
item.dc:creator: koolah
item.description: One egg on the sheet near this female. Shadow removed from beneath left forewing to make it more obvious. Moth was very restless - obviously not the expected place to lay eggs.
